interface for calling them.\n\nGiven the constraints, I think the best approach is to write a Node.js script that directly calls the MCP endpoint, or to use the openclaw-lark-tools package if it provides a CLI for this.\n\n\nI should explore whether the openclaw-lark package offers a direct mechanism for invoking the feishu_update_doc tool, since the CLI help shows it's registered but doesn't expose an obvious command for calling it.\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"我看到 `feishu_update_doc` 工具已经注册到 OpenClaw 运行时中。让我检查一下如何通过 CLI 调用这个工具:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_5cf3fe9ff4e648a595f2c5ed","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config get channels.feishu.mcpEndpoint 2>&1 || echo \"Checking alternative...\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"custom-dashscope-aliyuncs-com","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":6,"output":609,"cacheRead":22461,"cacheWrite":663,"totalTokens":23739,"cost":{"input":6.6e-7,"output":0.00017052000000000001,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00017118000000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774003782150}}
