ot_image\n[plugins] Registered all OAPI tools (calendar, task, bitable, search, drive, wiki, sheets, im)\n[plugins] feishu_doc: Registered feishu_fetch_doc, feishu_create_doc, feishu_update_doc\n[plugins] feishu_oauth: Registered feishu_oauth tool\n[plugins] feishu_oauth_batch_auth: Registered feishu_oauth_batch_auth tool\nerror: unknown command 'feishu_update_doc'\n\n(Command exited with code 1)","cwd":"/home/zhangyanbo/.openclaw/workspace-fox-feishu"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774003832285}}
{"type":"message","id":"0bbcb343","parentId":"a366247e","timestamp":"2026-03-20T10:50:36.817Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `feishu_update_doc` tool is registered in the OpenClaw runtime, but it isn’t exposed as a top‑level CLI command. Direct invocation via `openclaw feishu_update_doc …` therefore fails with “unknown command”. To update the document as requested, the tool must be called through the OpenClaw agent runtime (e.g., via an agent turn or a programmatic tool call). Since this subagent cannot directly invoke the MCP tool from the CLI, I’m unable to complete the update here. Further action would require the main agent to invoke `feishu_update_doc` with:\n\n- `doc_id: \"WyJgdbxKeoUMEExureDcR2Mjngd\"`\n- `mode: \"overwrite\"`\n- `markdown: <the full markdown content provided>`\n\nIf the main agent can perform that call, the document will be updated and the result returned."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":25014,"output":189,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25203,"cost":{"input":-25014,"output":-189,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-25203}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774003832290}}
